projects:
[{'title': 'Regulatory practices, competitive advantages and supply-demand chains between the countries of Paraguay-Parana Waterway Agreement of Fluvial Transport', 'date': {'start': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'River navigation in the Paraguay-Paraná Waterway is governed by the Agreement of River Transport by the Paraguay-Paraná Waterway, signed on June 26, 1992, in Las Leñas and internalized by Brazil through Decree No. 2,716 of August 10, 1998. The agreement provides for the removal of all administrative, regulatory and procedural barriers and constraints with a view to developing a flowing commerce and efficient river activity, reaffirming the principle of free navigation in rivers.
In its sphere of action, ANTAQ is responsible for representing Brazil together with international shipping agencies, as well as monitoring the transportation of cargo by Brazilian and foreign companies, promoting demand studies, fleet composition and the practice of chartering.
In the fulfillment of these attributions, it is verified that the volume of cargo of Brazilian origin transported in this waterway has grown significantly, however, with a reduction in the participation of Brazilian shipping companies. The 2013 Waterway Statistical Yearbook showed an average annual growth of 17% in tonnage transported in the last three years, projecting annual growth of 6.1% by 2030 (ANTAQ, 2013). At the same time, there was a 33% reduction in the fleet of Brazilian Shipping Companies, with a high index of ship aging due to lack of renewal, with the demand for transport services being met by the establishment of charter contracts for foreign vessels.
In this scenario, it is intended, through the present study, to identify the regulatory practices of the signatory countries of the agreement, pointing out possible competitive advantages and adequacy needs of the Brazilian legal-institutional framework, as well as providing subsidies to government decisions in monitoring the agreement and in the policy to support river transportation, based on the supply and demand of cargo transportation, with a view to fostering the development of the Paraguay-Paraná waterway.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Renata', 'last_name': 'Correia', 'name': None, 'headline': 'River Engineer at The Ocean Cleanup'}]}, {'title': 'Feasilibity Studies (Technical, Economical and Environmental) of Paraguay river Waterway', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}, 'end': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, 'description': None, 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Renata', 'last_name': 'Correia', 'name': None, 'headline': 'River Engineer at The Ocean Cleanup'}]}, {'title': 'Activated Sludge Sedimentation: Case Study of the Belem Sewage Treatment Plant (STP)', 'date': {'start': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2011}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2012}}, 'description': 'Projeto de Iniciação científica vinculado ao PROSAB (Programa de Saneamento Básico) na área de saneamento ambiental. O projeto contou com a execução de testes com lodos ativados na ETE Belém da Sanepar (Curitiba – PR) utilizando colunas de sedimentação de diversos volumes, no intuito de identificar características na sedimentação (velocidades, efeito parede), para posterior execução do dimensionamento de decantadores secundários.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Renata', 'last_name': 'Correia', 'name': None, 'headline': 'River Engineer at The Ocean Cleanup'}, {'type': 'nonStandardizedContributor', 'first_name': None, 'last_name': None, 'name': 'Miguel Mansur Aisse', 'headline': None}, {'type': 'nonStandardizedContributor', 'first_name': None, 'last_name': None, 'name': 'Francielle da Silva Maria', 'headline': None}]}]
